  "title": "Special Education Teacher (Primary School - Maths)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Working Hours: </strong>Monday to Friday (Except Wednesday), 7 am to 4 pm. Wednesday 7 am to 1.30 pm</p><p><strong>Working Location:</strong> Bukit Batok</p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Deliver clear and effective lessons using a variety of relevant teaching strategies for students with autism</li><li>Play an important role in the planning and development of curriculum and programmes to facilitate student learning</li><li>Exhibits deep commitment to the holistic education and development of students</li><li>Work collaboratively with a multi-disciplinary team and with parents in providing quality education and care for the students</li><li>Understand students' diverse learning and developmental needs, interests, abilities and potential through observations, diagnoses and discussions (with students, parents and colleagues), and adapts approaches accordingly</li><li>Work collaboratively with a multi-professional team and parents in providing quality education and feedback for students.</li><li>Plan and write IEP lesson plans, reports, records and documentation.</li><li>Guide and coach Teacher Aides</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Recognised Degree or Polytechnic Diploma</li><li><strong>Teaching qualifications or equivalent in Special Education is preferred</strong></li><li>5 credits in GCE 'O' level with a pass in English and Mathematics is mandatory</li><li>Preferably 3 years of experience at primary level</li><li>Familiar with national curriculum</li><li>Demonstrate passion in teaching</li><li>Experience in teaching children and youths with autism will be an added advantage</li></ul>",
